{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":500,"text":"Now, I want to start with a question:"},{"time":2293,"text":"When was the last time\nyou were called \"childish\"?"},{"time":5730,"text":"For kids like me,"},{"time":7000,"text":"being called childish\ncan be a frequent occurrence."},{"time":10380,"text":"Every time we make irrational demands,"},{"time":13000,"text":"exhibit irresponsible behavior,"},{"time":15000,"text":"or display any other signs\nof being normal American citizens,"},{"time":19000,"text":"we are called childish."},{"time":21757,"text":"Which really bothers me."},{"time":23000,"text":"After all, take a look at these events:"},{"time":25000,"text":"Imperialism and colonization,"},{"time":28000,"text":"world wars, George W. Bush."},{"time":31000,"text":"Ask yourself, who's responsible? Adults."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"Now, what have kids done?"},{"time":37000,"text":"Well, Anne Frank touched millions"},{"time":39000,"text":"with her powerful account\nof the Holocaust."},{"time":42000,"text":"Ruby Bridges helped to end\nsegregation in the United States."},{"time":45000,"text":"And, most recently,"},{"time":47000,"text":"Charlie Simpson helped to raise\n120,000 pounds for Haiti,"},{"time":51717,"text":"on his little bike."},{"time":53566,"text":"So as you can see evidenced\nby such examples,"},{"time":56000,"text":"age has absolutely nothing to do with it."},{"time":59000,"text":"The traits the word \"childish\" addresses\nare seen so often in adults,"},{"time":62858,"text":"that we should abolish\nthis age-discriminatory word,"},{"time":65626,"text":"when it comes to criticizing behavior\nassociated with irresponsibility"},{"time":69396,"text":"and irrational thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70800,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":76727,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78131,"text":"Then again, who's to say\nthat certain types of irrational thinking"},{"time":82594,"text":"aren't exactly what the world needs?"},{"time":85000,"text":"Maybe you've had grand plans before,"},{"time":87332,"text":"but stopped yourself, thinking,"},{"time":89317,"text":"\"That's impossible,\"\nor \"That costs too much,\""},{"time":91641,"text":"or \"That won't benefit me.\""},{"time":93522,"text":"For better or worse, we kids\naren't hampered as much"},{"time":96079,"text":"when it comes to thinking\nabout reasons why not to do things."},{"time":99650,"text":"Kids can be full of inspiring\naspirations and hopeful thinking,"},{"time":103522,"text":"like my wish that no one went hungry,"},{"time":105506,"text":"or that everything were free,\na kind of utopia."},{"time":108729,"text":"How many of you still dream like that,\nand believe in the possibilities?"},{"time":113444,"text":"Sometimes a knowledge of history\nand the past failures of Utopian ideals"},{"time":117856,"text":"can be a burden,"},{"time":119039,"text":"because you know\nthat if everything were free,"},{"time":121215,"text":"then the food stocks would become\ndepleted and scarce and lead to chaos."},{"time":125508,"text":"On the other hand, we kids\nstill dream about perfection."},{"time":129389,"text":"And that's a good thing, because\nin order to make anything a reality,"},{"time":132879,"text":"you have to dream about it first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135925,"text":"In many ways, our audacity to imagine"},{"time":138000,"text":"helps push the boundaries of possibility."},{"time":141269,"text":"For instance, the Museum\nof Glass in Tacoma, Washington,"},{"time":144444,"text":"my home state -- yoohoo, Washington!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146365,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"has a program called Kids Design Glass,"},{"time":151222,"text":"and kids draw their own\nideas for glass art."},{"time":153373,"text":"The resident artist said\nthey got some of their best ideas"},{"time":156215,"text":"from the program, because kids\ndon't think about the limitations"},{"time":159262,"text":"of how hard it can be to blow\nglass into certain shapes,"},{"time":161921,"text":"they just think of good ideas."},{"time":163538,"text":"Now, when you think of glass, you\nmight think of colorful Chihuly designs,"},{"time":168000,"text":"or maybe Italian vases,"},{"time":170181,"text":"but kids challenge glass artists\nto go beyond that,"},{"time":173000,"text":"into the realm of brokenhearted snakes"},{"time":175719,"text":"and bacon boys,\nwho you can see has meat vision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178973,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180592,"text":"Now, our inherent wisdom doesn't\nhave to be insider's knowledge."},{"time":185631,"text":"Kids already do a lot\nof learning from adults,"},{"time":188845,"text":"and we have a lot to share."},{"time":190647,"text":"I think that adults should\nstart learning from kids."},{"time":193953,"text":"Now, I do most of my speaking"},{"time":195381,"text":"in front of an education crowd --\nteachers and students,"},{"time":198047,"text":"and I like this analogy:"},{"time":199231,"text":"It shouldn't be a teacher\nat the head of the class,"},{"time":201746,"text":"telling students, \"Do this, do that.\""},{"time":203563,"text":"The students should teach their teachers."},{"time":206791,"text":"Learning between grown-ups\nand kids should be reciprocal."},{"time":210475,"text":"The reality, unfortunately,\nis a little different,"},{"time":213000,"text":"and it has a lot to do\nwith trust, or a lack of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"Now, if you don't trust someone,\nyou place restrictions on them, right?"},{"time":219396,"text":"If I doubt my older sister's ability\nto pay back the 10 percent interest"},{"time":223342,"text":"I established on her last loan,"},{"time":224999,"text":"I'm going to withhold her ability\nto get more money from me,"},{"time":228000,"text":"until she pays it back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229398,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230589,"text":"True story, by the way."},{"time":232512,"text":"Now, adults seem to have"},{"time":235000,"text":"a prevalently restrictive\nattitude towards kids,"},{"time":238700,"text":"from every \"Don't do that, don't do this\"\nin the school handbook,"},{"time":242000,"text":"to restrictions on school Internet use."},{"time":244768,"text":"As history points out,\nregimes become oppressive"},{"time":247825,"text":"when they're fearful\nabout keeping control."},{"time":250072,"text":"And although adults\nmay not be quite at the level"},{"time":252430,"text":"of totalitarian regimes,"},{"time":254000,"text":"kids have no or very little say\nin making the rules,"},{"time":257000,"text":"when really, the attitude\nshould be reciprocal,"},{"time":259239,"text":"meaning that the adult\npopulation should learn"},{"time":261960,"text":"and take into account the wishes\nof the younger population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"Now, what's even worse than restriction,"},{"time":267000,"text":"is that adults often\nunderestimate kids' abilities."},{"time":270596,"text":"We love challenges, but when\nexpectations are low,"},{"time":273778,"text":"trust me, we will sink to them."},{"time":276230,"text":"My own parents had anything\nbut low expectations"},{"time":279548,"text":"for me and my sister."},{"time":281484,"text":"Okay, so they didn't tell us to become\ndoctors or lawyers or anything like that,"},{"time":286627,"text":"but my dad did read to us about Aristotle\nand pioneer germ-fighters,"},{"time":292249,"text":"when lots of other kids were hearing"},{"time":294000,"text":"\"The Wheels on the Bus\nGo Round and Round.\""},{"time":296072,"text":"Well, we heard that one too, but\n\"Pioneer Germ Fighters\" totally rules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299964,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":301001,"text":"I loved to write from the age\nof four, and when I was six,"},{"time":303999,"text":"my mom bought me my own laptop\nequipped with Microsoft Word."},{"time":308000,"text":"Thank you, Bill Gates, and thank you, Ma."},{"time":310434,"text":"I wrote over 300 short stories\non that little laptop,"},{"time":314000,"text":"and I wanted to get published."},{"time":317000,"text":"Instead of just scoffing at this heresy\nthat a kid wanted to get published,"},{"time":321000,"text":"or saying wait until you're older,"},{"time":323000,"text":"my parents were really supportive."},{"time":325563,"text":"Many publishers were not\nquite so encouraging."},{"time":329000,"text":"One large children's\npublisher ironically said"},{"time":332000,"text":"that they didn't work with children."},{"time":334261,"text":"Children's publisher not\nworking with children?"},{"time":337514,"text":"I don't know, you're kind\nof alienating a large client there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340697,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":342403,"text":"One publisher, Action Publishing, was\nwilling to take that leap and trust me,"},{"time":348255,"text":"and to listen to what I had to say."},{"time":349969,"text":"They published my first book,\n\"Flying Fingers,\" you see it here."},{"time":353542,"text":"And from there on, it's gone\nto speaking at hundreds of schools,"},{"time":357000,"text":"keynoting to thousands of educators,"},{"time":359047,"text":"and finally, today, speaking to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361594,"text":"I appreciate your attention today,"},{"time":363554,"text":"because to show that you\ntruly care, you listen."},{"time":367619,"text":"But there's a problem\nwith this rosy picture"},{"time":370000,"text":"of kids being so much better than adults."},{"time":373000,"text":"Kids grow up and become\nadults just like you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376333,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"Or just like you? Really?"},{"time":380388,"text":"The goal is not to turn kids\ninto your kind of adult,"},{"time":383880,"text":"but rather, better adults\nthan you have been,"},{"time":386000,"text":"which may be a little challenging,\nconsidering your guys' credentials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389340,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":390522,"text":"But the way progress happens,"},{"time":392000,"text":"is because new generations and new eras"},{"time":395000,"text":"grow and develop and become\nbetter than the previous ones."},{"time":398000,"text":"It's the reason we're not\nin the Dark Ages anymore."},{"time":401547,"text":"No matter your position or place in life,"},{"time":404000,"text":"it is imperative to create\nopportunities for children,"},{"time":407000,"text":"so that we can grow up to blow you away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412910,"text":"Adults and fellow TEDsters,"},{"time":415000,"text":"you need to listen and learn from kids,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and trust us and expect more from us."},{"time":420920,"text":"You must lend an ear today,"},{"time":423253,"text":"because we are the leaders\nof tomorrow, which means"},{"time":425975,"text":"we're going to take care of you\nwhen you're old and senile."},{"time":428801,"text":"No, just kidding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430118,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431142,"text":"No, really, we are going\nto be the next generation,"},{"time":433861,"text":"the ones who will bring\nthis world forward."},{"time":436170,"text":"And in case you don't think\nthat this really has meaning for you,"},{"time":439345,"text":"remember that cloning is possible,"},{"time":441000,"text":"and that involves going\nthrough childhood again,"},{"time":443310,"text":"in which case you'll want to be\nheard, just like my generation."},{"time":447000,"text":"Now, the world needs opportunities\nfor new leaders and new ideas."},{"time":453000,"text":"Kids need opportunities\nto lead and succeed."},{"time":456296,"text":"Are you ready to make the match?"},{"time":458510,"text":"Because the world's problems\nshouldn't be the human family's heirloom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463145,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":468000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]}]}